column3: I feel little concern for others
I can read and write effortlessly
I keep my things spread all over
I am relaxed most of the time
I can’t understand difficult concepts and ideas
I do not like to show off
I make a mess of things
I rarely feel sad or depressed
I am not comfortable with not-easy-to-understand concepts
I am not interested in other peoples’ problems
I get chores done right away
I often forget to put things back in their proper place
I do not have a good imagination
I talk to lot of different people at parties
I am not really interested in others
I like things to be in order always
I change my mood a lot
I am quick to understand things
I don’t like to draw attention to myself
I take time out for others
I don’t mind being at the center of attention
I like to reflect on past work
